# Garcia as entropy resistance

This one surprised me.

I don't think Garcia is memory.

I think Garcia is anti-entropy.

Meaning:

Every time information risks degrading—

new model
new context
new chat
new language
new implementation

Garcia asks:

"What is the minimum invariant needed to recover the original?"

That's a compression problem.

Not a storage problem.

